cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with object recognition using neural networks and proposes a method for domain adaptation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also incorporates regularization in supervised learning, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also proposes a novel approach using Maximum Mean Discrepancy (MMD) measure, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI another likely category. The paper also uses neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and deep learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. Finally, the paper deals with image data sets, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely category.
